name: So I Married an Anti-Fan
overview: The romance between top star Hoo Joon and his anti-fan reporter Lee Geun-young who end up living together.

episodes.name: How Could Anyone Be This Different from Me?
episodes.overview: Kpop artist Who Joon comes back to Korea and almost immediately makes a bad impression on journalist Geun-young and her life.

episodes.name: Are You Brave Enough to Be Hated?
episodes.overview: Geun-young embraces her new anti-fan status but starts to regret being so easily recognized. Who Joon is irritated by Geun-young's antics and the inconvenience that she is causing him.

guest_stars.character: Chief Producer of the Reality Show
guest_stars.name: Jeon Hun-tae

episodes.name: Reality, Something Between Somewhat and Somehow
episodes.overview: Geun-young and Who Joon do their first shoot together and things take a dramatic turn when they get into an accident. Who Joon and JJ get into an argument over In-hyung and Geun-young.

episodes.name: You and I... It's An Incident Or An Accident?
episodes.overview: Geun-young makes a mistake on set and goes to find Who Joon to apologize only to see In-hyung again but still unable to see who she is. Who Joon tries to distance himself from JJ and In-hyung but somehow gets dragged back in.

episodes.name: Where I Belong and Where I Don’t
episodes.overview: After meeting Roy and seeing her portrayal in the trailer of the show, Geun-young starts to look for a job second-guessing signing on to the show. Who Joon runs into JJ and the two end up getting into a physical fight.

episodes.name: If I Had Never Met You
episodes.overview: The reality show moves to Japan because Who Joon has a commercial shoot there. Who Joon and JJ both find out that In-hyung is to co-star in the commercial causing more friction between them that spills out and gets noticed by Geun-young.

guest_stars.character: Flight Attendant Who Asks for Autograph
guest_stars.name: Lim Ji-Min

episodes.name: You Make Me Worry...
episodes.overview: After returning from Japan, Geun-young realizes that being on a reality show is hard work. Geun-young also starts to put together Who Joon and In-hyung's past relationship.

guest_stars.character: Flight Stewardess That Helps Who Joon
guest_stars.name: Song Ji-eun

episodes.name: What Doesn't Fit You Always Becomes a Problem
episodes.overview: Who Joon and Geun-young start to warm up to each other, but Who Joon's past complicates things. JJ's inability to let Who Joon go creates more problems for Who Joon.

guest_stars.character: Guy Waiting in Line with Friend (Denim Jacket)
guest_stars.name: Koo Ja-keon

episodes.name: The Two Just Can't Ever Get Close
episodes.overview: Who Joon tries to mend his relationship with Geun-young even though Geun-young misunderstands his motives. JJ continues to investigate Who Joon and runs into a clue accidentally given to him by Geun-young.

episodes.name: When You Have Someone Else To Protect
episodes.overview: Who Joon finds out about Yu-ri and decides to go on a road trip with her and Geun-young. JJ and In-hyung's relationship gets more complicated after the interview with Who Joon.

episodes.name: Sometimes You Have to Pick Your Side
episodes.overview: Who Joon rushes to the hospital with Geun-young to see In-hyung. Geun-young stays the night with In-hyung to make sure that she is recovering. Who Joon gets kidnapped by a fan, and Geun-young and Ji-hyang try to find him.

episodes.name: Was It Twist of Fate That Brought Us Here?
episodes.overview: Who Joon and Geun-young grow closer and define their relationship though they are keeping it a secret. In-hyung starts to move on from JJ and realizes she has more people on her side than she thought.

episodes.name: A Dangerous Invitation
episodes.overview: While the rumors about Who Joon and In-hyung persist, JJ shares new information about Who Joon with Young-seok, hoping that Young-seok will come to his side. Who Joon and Geun-young go to the beach to shoot for their show.

episodes.name: This Won't Be The End
episodes.overview: With their show ending, Geun-young and Who Joon navigate the new phase of their relationship only to be hit by two different scandals consecutively. The outcome has far-reaching effects that lead to tragedy and the end of relationships.

episodes.name: The Truth Untold
episodes.overview: Overwhelmed with the fallout from his press conference, the accident, and trying to find his father, Who Joon decides to take a step back. Geun-young gives him space while trying to help him using the media.

episodes.name: I'll Stand by You Until the End of Time
episodes.overview: In-hyung and JJ are recovering in the hospital after their and each reflects on their past relationships and mistakes. Geun-young and Who Joon focus on their careers and relationship, hoping to leave their problems behind.
